snippet.textDisplay:
I think this has been one of my favorite battles so far, if mostly for the way they all acted during the judging. The camaraderie and genuine desire to share what they’ve made and please their friends with their cooking reminds me a lot about the best relationships I’ve had with fellow line cooks. It’s an amazing feeling to impress a customer with a dish of yours, but impressing a fellow chef that you love and respect? Nothing beats that feeling.

All of their battles are hilarious and fun to watch, but I love when they take a break every once in a while and genuinely compliment each other’s cooking. You can tell how much it means to them. I think it’s why Sorted has been my favorite food channel for years.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: Idea for one of the next Pass it on challenges: pair cooking. So establish the order, then make the guys cook in pairs: 1 and 2, pass it to 3 and 4, then 5 and 1, 2 and 3 and finally, 4 and 5. Even though this will mean one person will participate both in rounds 1 and 3, relatively close to each other, I think, the overall mess in doing it this way will make it fun. And this will allow them to actually make some plans, oven, fridge and microwave. Or even do it the "remote controlled" way, the same order.
